ontocomAgent.ontology
Class MethodsSPARQL

java.lang.Object
  ontocomAgent.ontology.MethodsSPARQL
Direct Known Subclasses:
OntologyOnline
public class MethodsSPARQL
extends java.lang.Object

This class was built to implement methods that facilitate the use and handling of the SPARQL queries in framework Jena (Jena Project). There is also here string manipulations. Is recommended to access the project site Jena and read the initials tutorials, if any doubts arise about some methods used here. However I am available for any discussion.

References used:
OpenTox - Querying/Reasoning with Jena and SPARQL
Jena - Documentação da API ARQ (querys)
IBM DeveloperWorks - Search RDF data with SPARQL
Semantic Web.com - Fórum de dúvidas sobre variados códigos
Stackoverflow - Outro bom fórum sobre variados códigos

getLitRes

public void getLitRes(java.lang.String queryString,
                      java.lang.String var1,
                      java.lang.String var2)

EXPERIMENTAL. This is a method example to obtain a columns treatment in an SPARL query Returns the result of the following SPARQL query:

SELECT ?Element ?Name WHERE { ?Element <http://www.owl-ontologies.com/ontology.owl#Name> ?Name.FILTER regex(?Name,'Beatriz') . }

Manipulating each column and value (?Element, ?Name), verifying that data are literals or resources on Ontology. Each column is treated as a variable at node RDF.

Parameters:
queryString - A string containing the query mentioned above.
var1 - In this example the will handle column ?Name.
var2 - In this example the will handle column ?Element.

getArrayIndValue

public java.lang.String[] getArrayIndValue(java.lang.String queryString,
                                           java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> listColumns)

Performs a query and return in an array of two positions, the first column responsible for the resource (individual) and the second by the given literal. Use queries (queryString) that can return only one result row (a column with another resource and the resource value).

Parameters:
queryString - Query to be held.
listColumns - An ArrayList with the name of the two columns surveyed in queryString (beginning with '?')
Returns:
Array with 2 results, odd positions with the column name, even positions with value name that came the query.

getObjectRelationProperty

public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> getObjectRelationProperty(java.lang.String propertyURI,
                                                                       java.lang.String rdfTag)
This method uses SPARQL conducting research in ontology about an object property and to whom it relates. For example, inserting a URI to an object property and informing on rdfTag "range", this method returns a list with the names of the target resource (rdf: range) inserted property

Parameters:
propertyURI - URI of a property.
rdfTag - a rdfs tag name like "range", "domain", etc.
Returns:
list with relations found.
